cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IT

The paper deals with machine learning methods applied to medical image analysis, specifically MRI data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel intensity normalisation scheme based on density matching, which involves modelling histograms as Dirichlet process Gaussian mixtures. This suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a mass-conserving flow to maintain agreement with the moving density, which could potentially fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
